```suggestion
  rw [tan_eq_sin_div_cos, sin_pi_div_six, cos_pi_div_six]
  ring
Same here.
My reading of the style guide is that putting each tactic call on a single line is slightly preferred. Can you do this (also in the other places)?

Existing code in `Arctan.lean` already contains some instances of multiple tactics on the same line (e.g. `arctan_eq_arccos`). I'm keeping my own instances of this in `Arctan.lean` but not in `Basic.lean`.
Can you indent these subgoals with a focusing dot also?
Done.
Is there only one such formula? Would putting this in the docstring be helpful? (I wouldn't have recognised the name, for instance.)
Can to put these lemmas into a separate section, as appropriate, and mention them in the module docstring?
Done.
Since you're only using this once, I would inline it in the proof of `arctan_add` directly.
At this point, you have two goals. This should show up in the proof structure, with focusing dots.
The assumption `x ^ 2 < 1` would be more standard, or even better two assumptions `-1 < x` and `x < 1`.

```suggestion
  rw [arctan_add] <;> norm_num
```
Same thing below.
All done.
